# Date Format Rule

The entire MyChair application MUST display dates in **DD/MM/YYYY** format.

Applies everywhere user-facing:

- forms & date pickers
- tables
- payroll, monthly salary, salary history
- employee module (joining date)
- exports / salary slips / invoices

## Frontend

- Use `formatDateDMY(dateInput)` from `src/utils/utilities.ts` for ALL date display.
  Do not hand-roll `toLocaleDateString`, `MM/DD/YYYY`, `DD MMM YYYY`, etc. for new code.
- For `<input type="date">`, store/transport the value as ISO (`YYYY-MM-DD`) using
  `toDateInputValue(...)`, but always display the human-readable value via `formatDateDMY`.
- Never introduce `MM/DD/YYYY` (US) date strings in UI.

## Backend / API

- Dates are stored and returned as UTC ISO 8601 (the frontend formats to DD/MM/YYYY).
- Month/year driven data (e.g. payroll) is transported as integers (`month`, `year`).

## Rationale

Salon owners are non-technical and span regions where DD/MM/YYYY is expected.
A single shared formatter prevents inconsistent date rendering across modules.
